description.text:
Print and enjoy. You can use the &quot;awesome.stl&quot; as a pattern with openscad to print a postive or negative image on all kinds of things.
I haven't printed this yet. Until I can test they work for sure I am leaving this a work in progress.
Sample Openscad Script to get some flames.
difference()<br />
{<br />
rotate([180,0,0])<br />
translate([-38,75,-11])<br />
import(file=&quot;iphone4g.stl&quot;);
<code >intersection()
{
    cube([50,80,3.2],true);
    scale([1.5,1.5,2.5])
    import(file="awesome.stl");
}</code>
}
